'''H.A.M. robes''' are the [[clothes|uniform]] worn by the [[Humans Against Monsters]] cult. They can be obtained by pickpocketing [[Male H.A.M. member|male]] and [[Female H.A.M. member|female]] H.A.M. members using the [[Thieving]] skill or by killing [[H.A.M. Guard]]s. While wearing parts of this outfit, players are slightly less likely to be kicked out of the [[H.A.M. Hideout]] when failing to pickpocket H.A.M. members, with the effect increasing with the number of pieces worn.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/751400357473947648|date=8 July 2016|archiveurl=https://archive.is/xoE62|archivedate=20 December 2019|quote=HAM kit doesn't reduce getting caught, but each piece makes you slightly less likely to be ejected after being caught.}}

A robe top, robe bottom, and hood are acquired during [[The Lost Tribe]]. Two full sets are needed for [[Death to the Dorgeshuun]]. During Death to the Dorgeshuun, the chance to receive robe pieces is considerably higher.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1112039679547850752|date=30 March 2018|archiveurl=https://archive.is/3JZZ6|archivedate=28 May 2020|quote=Are you on the bit of the quest where you need it? If so, the chance of you getting HAM kit is considerably higher.}}

Players can store a complete set of H.A.M. robes in the [[armour case]] of the [[costume room]] of their [[player-owned house]].

After [[Death to the Dorgeshuun]] is completed, only the [[Ham robe]] and [[Ham boots]] serve a purpose, both used for [[easy clues]].

